{
  "title": "Hooks Reference",
  "slug": "hooks",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Hooks Reference"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Hooks are shell scripts that fire during agent activity and write events to .moatlog/events-YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl. moatlog init wires them automatically — this page is for reference and customization."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "How hooks are wired"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Cursor"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        { "type": "text", "value": "Config file: " },
        { "type": "inlineCode", "value": ".cursor/hooks.json" },
        { "type": "text", "value": ". Script location: " },
        { "type": "inlineCode", "value": ".cursor/hooks/" },
        { "type": "text", "value": " (" },
        { "type": "inlineCode", "value": "moatlog-event.sh" },
        { "type": "text", "value": ", " },
        { "type": "inlineCode", "value": "moatlog-distill.sh" },
        { "type": "text", "value": ")." }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Cursor hook events that trigger moatlog and the moatlog action they produce:"
